@section Binding accessors and mutators


The syntaxes described in this section allow the use of dot notation to
access class fields and to apply class methods.  The core syntaxes are
@func{with-fields}, @func{setf} and @func{getf}.

We have to be careful when using this notation: many macros are written
assuming that it is safe to reference identifiers multiple times, under
the assumption that identifier's reference has no side effects; this is
no more sure when using identifier syntaxes to access virtual class
fields.  As a style rule: it is better to always keep virtual fields
access free of side effects (unless really needed).

