@deffn Syntax letrec/with-class (((@ameta{var} @ametao{class name} @ameta{class name} ...) @ameta{init}) ...) @ameta{body}
Like @func{letrec} but automatically enclose the body in a
@func{with-fields} syntax using the specified class types.  Each
@meta{var} element can be one among:

@example
@ameta{id}
(@ameta{id} @ametao{class name} @ameta{class name} ...)
@end example

@noindent
in which: @meta{id} must be an identifier representing the variable
name, @ameta{class name} must be an identifier representing a class
name.

