@subsubsection Dynamic loading of libraries


A foreign shared library loadable with the @cfunc{dlopen} @posix{}
interface is called @dfn{shared object}.  Under @value{PACKAGE}, a
shared object can be opened, but not closed.  The @api{} makes use of a
Scheme object to represent a shared object; it allows access to all the
functions and variables exported by the library.

The following bindings are exported by the @library{ffi primitives}
library and reexported by the @library{ffi} compound library.


@defun open-shared-object @var{library-name}
Open a foreign shared library on the host system and return a shared
object; shared objects are disjoint from the other Scheme object types.

If opening the shared library fails: throw a continuable exception with
@func{raise-shared-object-opening-error}.  @ref{ffi core conditions
opening, Shared objects opening error}.

@var{library-name} must be a Scheme string or symbol representing the
file name or pathname to be opened; examples: @samp{zlib.so},
@samp{zlib.dylib}, @samp{zlib.dll}.  In the case of a name (without
directory part) the search path for shared objects is implemenation
dependent.

@quotation
@strong{For Unix} We can find documentation about the search path of
shared objects in the manual page of @cfunc{dlopen}.
@end quotation
@end defun


@defun shared-object? @var{obj}
Return true if @var{obj} is a shared object.
@end defun


@defun lookup-shared-object @var{shared} @var{foreign-symbol}
Search the shared object referenced by @var{shared} for an exported
symbol matching @var{foreign-symbol}, which must be a Scheme symbol or
string, and return its address as a pointer object.  @ref{ffi core
pointers, Pointer objects}.

If the foreign symbol is not found: raise a continuable exception with
@func{raise-shared-object-lookup-error}.  @ref{ffi core conditions
lookup, Shared objects lookup error}.
@end defun


@defvr Constant libc-shared-object
Bound to the shared object value identifying the C language runtime
library.  Notice that we can configure this value at installation time,
with the @option{--with-libc-shared-object} option to the
@command{configure} script.
@end defvr

