@subsubsection Utility macros


The following bindings are exported by the @library{ffi utilities}
library and reexported by the compound library @library{ffi}.


@deffn Syntax define-shared-object @ameta{name} @ameta{library-name}
Expands to:

@example
(define @meta{name}
  (open-shared-object* @meta{library-name}))
@end example
@end deffn


@deffn Syntax make-c-callout* @ameta{ret-type} @ameta{address} (@ameta{arg-type0} @ameta{arg-type} ...)
@deffnx Syntax make-c-callout/with-errno* @ameta{ret-type} @ameta{address} (@ameta{arg-type0} @ameta{arg-type} ...)
Wrappers for the @func{make-c-callout} functions which allow us not to
quote the arguments.

The type symbols in @ameta{ret-type} and @ameta{arg-type} can be
elements of the enumeration @code{clang-external-types} or custom type
symbols bound to a symbol in the enumeration.
@end deffn


@deffn Syntax make-c-function* @ameta{shared-object} @ameta{ret-type} @ameta{funcname} (@ameta{arg-type0} @ameta{arg-type} ...)
@deffnx Syntax make-c-function/with-errno* @ameta{shared-object} @ameta{ret-type} @ameta{funcname} (@ameta{arg-type0} @ameta{arg-type} ...)
Wrappers for the @func{make-c-function} functions which determine the
address of the function by looking for the @ameta{funcname} symbol in
the @ameta{shared-object}.

The type symbols in @ameta{ret-type} and @ameta{arg-type} can be
elements of the enumeration @code{clang-external-types} or custom type
symbols bound to a symbol in the enumeration.

As an example, the main deflate functions from Zlib can be defined with:

@example
(define zlib-shared-object
  (open-shared-object* 'libz.so))

(define deflateInit
  (make-c-function* zlib-shared-object
                    int deflateInit_ (pointer int)))

(define deflate
  (make-c-function* zlib-shared-object
                    int deflate (pointer int)))

(define deflateEnd
  (make-c-function* zlib-shared-object
                    int deflateEnd (pointer)))
@end example

@noindent
but we can also take advantage of these macro features to define them
like this:

@example
(define zlib-shared-object
  (open-shared-object* 'libz.so))

(define z_streamp 'pointer)

(define deflateInit
  (make-c-function* zlib-shared-object
                    int deflateInit_ (z_streamp int)))

(define deflate
  (make-c-function* zlib-shared-object
                    int deflate (z_streamp int)))

(define deflateEnd
  (make-c-function* zlib-shared-object
                    int deflateEnd (z_streamp)))
@end example

@noindent
where the binding for @samp{z_streamp} is recognised as a custom type
and expanded to @samp{pointer}.

Variadic functions, like @cfunc{fprintf}, are @strong{not} supported,
but we can interface with them by fixing the arguments; for example:

@example
(define uuid-shared-object
  (open-shared-object* 'libuuid.so))

(define uuid_make
  (let ((arg-2  (make-c-function* uuid-shared-object
                  int uuid_make (void* unsigned-int)))
        (arg-4  (make-c-function* uuid-shared-object
                  int uuid_make
                  (void* unsigned-int void* char*))))
    (case-lambda
     ((*id mode)
      (arg-2 *id mode))
     ((*id mode uuid name)
      (arg-4 *id mode uuid name)))))
@end example
@end deffn


@deffn Syntax make-c-callback* @ameta{ret-type} @ameta{scheme-proc} (@ameta{arg-type0} @ameta{arg-type} ...)
Wrapper for the @func{make-c-callback} function which allows us not to
quote the arguments.
@end deffn


@deffn Syntax define-c-functions @ameta{lib-spec} (@ameta{pub-name} (@ameta{ret-type} @ameta{funcname} (@ameta{arg-type0} @ameta{arg-type} ...))) ...
@deffnx Syntax define-c-functions/with-errno @ameta{lib-spec} (@ameta{pub-name} (@ameta{ret-type} @ameta{funcname} (@ameta{arg-type0} @ameta{arg-type} ...))) ...
An interface to the above macros.  Example:

@example
(define-shared-object zlib-shared-object 'libz.so)

(define z_streamp 'void*)

(define-c-functions zlib-shared-object
  (deflateInit  (int deflateInit_ (z_streamp int)))
  (deflate      (int deflate      (z_streamp int)))
  (deflateEnd   (int deflateEnd   (z_streamp))))
@end example
@end deffn

