@subsubsection Low level interface


The following bindings are exported by the @library{ffi platform}
library.  This interface adapts the Scheme implementation @ffi{} to the
requirements of the Nausicaa distribution.


@defun open-shared-object @var{library-name}
Open a shared library and return its reference object.
@var{library-name} must be a Scheme string representing the file name or
pathname to be opened.  If the foreign symbol is not found: raise a
continuable exception with @func{raise-shared-object-opening-error}.
@end defun


@defun lookup-shared-object @var{library-reference} @var{foreign-symbol}
Search the shared object referenced by @var{library-reference} for an
exported symbol matching @var{foreign-symbol}, which must be a Scheme
string, and return its address as pointer object.  If the operation
fails: raise a continuable exception with components @condition{who},
@condition{message}, @condition{shared-object-lookup-error},
@condition{foreign-symbol}.
@end defun


@defun make-c-callout @var{ret-type} @var{address} @var{arg-types}
@defunx make-c-callout/with-errno @var{ret-type} @var{address} @var{arg-types}
Build and return a new callout closure wrapping a foreign function
referenced by the pointer object @var{address}.

@var{ret-type} must be a Scheme symbol in the enumeration
@code{enum-clang-types}, representing the C language data type of the
foreign function's return value.

@var{arg-types} must be a list of Scheme symbols in the enumeration
@code{enum-clang-types}, representing the C language data types of the
foreign function's arguments.  To specify a foreign function accepting
no arguments, @var{arg-types} must be @code{(void)}.

Variadic functions are not supported.
@end defun


@defun make-c-callback @var{ret-type} @var{scheme-function} @var{arg-types}
Build and return a new pointer value referencing a callback object; the
callback, when invoked, applies the scheme function

@var{ret-type} must be a Scheme symbol in the enumeration
@code{enum-clang-types}, representing the C language data type of the
foreign function's return value.

@var{arg-types} must be a list of Scheme symbols in the enumeration
@code{enum-clang-types}, representing the C language data types of the
foreign function's arguments.  To specify a foreign function accepting
no arguments, @var{arg-types} must be @code{(void)}.

Variadic functions are not supported.
@end defun


@defun free-c-callback @var{callback-pointer}
