@subsection Generating an interface


This section documents the @library{ffi inspector-maker} library, which
provides some automation in the generation of the infrastructure
required by interfaces to foreign, C language, libraries.  At present
this library is for internal use, so Nausicaa's end users can just
ignore it.

The library is meant to be loaded by a Scheme program, which generates a
set of files required by the interface; the program's file should be in
the top directory of the Nausicaa project.  For an interface to Libxml2
using the @code{xml libxml2} prefix for libraries, in a typical Nausicaa
project source tree, the files are:

@table @file
@item configuration/libxml2-inspector.m4
A @gnu{} Autoconf script defining a single @command{m4} macro to be used
by the @file{configure.ac} template to inspect the foreign library.  The
@file{aclocal.m4} file must include the line:

@example
m4_include(configuration/libxml2-inspector.m4)
@end example

@noindent
and the @file{configure.ac} template must include the macro call:

@example
NAUSICAA_LIBXML
@end example

@noindent
where @code{NAUSICAA_LIBXML} is the name of the macro.

@item src/libraries/xml/libxml2/sizeof.sls.in
A template for the @library{xml libxml2 sizeof} library holding foreign
data types inspection definitions and constants definitions.  It is
meant  to be processed by the @command{configure} script to insert
values for the @code{@@...@@} symbols.

@item src/libraries/xml/libxml2/structs.sls
A library defining class types to make it easier to access C structures
fields with dot notation.
@end table

